					</pre>


<font size=+1><b>Table of Contents</b><p>
</font>						<img src="/imgs/wee-page.gif" align=left>
						<a href="#SUB1">Expenses: The inner Chambers</a><p>
						<img src="/imgs/wee-page.gif" align=left>
						<a href="#SUB2">Chambers Development didn't go into much detail about its deferred costs; investors should have asked.</a><p>
						<img src="/imgs/wee-page.gif" align=left>
						<a href="#SUB3">Quality of Earnings: The lesson of Education Alternatives</a><p>
						<img src="/imgs/wee-page.gif" align=left>
						<a href="#SUB4">Education Alternatives showed an operating loss, offset by income from other sources.</a><p>
						<img src="/imgs/wee-page.gif" align=left>
						<a href="#SUB5">Depreciation: A distorted image for American Shared</a><p>
						<img src="/imgs/wee-page.gif" align=left>
						<a href="#SUB6">Lower quarterly depreciation expenses at American Shared Hospital Services spoke to internal troubles.</a><p>
					</font>
					<p>

<font size=+1><b>Company Index</b><br>
</font>						<a href="#NASD:EAIN">Education Alternatives, Inc.</a><br>

						<a href="#AMEX:AMS">American Shared Hospital Services</a><br>

					<p>

					<p>
	
		
</td>
