<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 11/06/96 -- Greg Dorsey, editor of the Web-based "DollarWise Investing" </title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6007.html?worth+PCFN25.gif+Transcripts>
<img src="/ads/PCFN25.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>11/06/96 -- Greg Dorsey, editor of the Web-based "DollarWise Investing" </b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						On Wednesday, November 6, Greg Dorsey joined Worth OnLine for "Conference Call." Dorsey is editor of the Web-based "DollarWise Investing," which analyzes underfollowed, undervalued stocks selling for less than $25 a share. Prior to starting DollarWise Investing, Mr. Dorsey edited "Wall Street Bargains," a monthly newsletter devoted to low-priced small stocks and mutual funds. He is also currently an associate editor at the award-winning "Personal Finance" newsletter. The opinions expressed within are those of Dorsey, and do not necessarily represent those of Worth OnLine, Worth magazine, or Capital Publishing.<p>
WorthEdit1:     Welcome, Mr. Dorsey. We'll begin with a question that was posted on our message boards. Adman495 asks: Recent articles have stated that Qualcomm stock is heading for a fall,<p>
GDorsey1:     It seems the market is on fire. But most of this is blue chips. Qualcomm could be headed for a fall. Chart sure looks ugly. Wall St. expecting $1.25 next year. Could be hard to meet. No room for error.<p>
WorthEdit1:     Should small stocks investors be excited about the rally in the past few days?<p>
GDorsey1:     WorthEdit1: Small stocks have barely budged in last few days. Don't expect much more for blue chips near term.<p>
BABY SOROS:     What are your opinions on two small cap stocks- SMTC and DOCSF.<p>
GDorsey1:     Baby Soros: PCDocs--don't think much of it. Prefer Fulcrum FULCF also down big.<p>
Sdray112:     Opinion on THDO (3 DO)?  Thanks<p>
GDorsey1:     Not much future in 3 DO.<p>
RKanterman:     How can we get your newsletter?<p>
GDorsey1:     I'm glad you asked. Write us a 1750 Old Meadow Rd., Suite 300, McLean, VA 22102.<p>
FRANK16145:     What about ZTEC? It has some great numbers.<p>
GDorsey1:     Frank: Regarding ZTEC--looks interesting, but will always trade at low P/E since it's a commodity player.<p>
Ksp001:     Any thoughts on IMAT ?<p>
GDorsey1:     Ksp001: Oil stocks are hot now. They've pulled back a bit here, but I'm looking for much higher oil prices over the next several years. Check out NBR, RB, FLCN; all drillers.<p>
FRANK16145:     What banks in the 20 or so dollar range look good..??<p>
GDorsey1:     Frank: Silicon Valley Bancshares is an excellent choice in that range.<p>
SCavett441:     Bethlehem Steel?<p>
GDorsey1:     SCavett: Beth Steel is an interesting speculation, could do 70-80 cents next year.<p>
BABY SOROS:     What else do you like besides oil stocks?<p>
GDorsey1:     Copper for the same reason as oil. Strong worldwide demand. Asarco is fave.<p>
FRANK16145:     What about TRK??<p>
GDorsey1:     TRK--racing is hot these days. Strong gate sales should lead to strong earnings. Buy.<p>
Charchy:     What P/E does 70-80 put Beth Steel at? I know their book value is @ 8.<p>
GDorsey1:     Beth Steel is fairly valued now. But with worldwide growth sparking those projections could be low.<p>
BABY SOROS:     Greg- do you take a bottom up approach or a top down (a macro or micro approach)?<p>
GDorsey1:     A little of both. Look for both broad economic trends and then examine best stocks in categories likely to benefit.<p>
BABY SOROS:     So, therefore you see the oils and coppers moving upward- any sectors you see as pans?<p>
GDorsey1:     PC manufacturers.<p>
RKanterman:     Greg, do you recommend any restaurants?<p>
GDorsey1:     RKanterman: CBRL, stock has come down here.<p>
FRANK16145:     What sector excites you the most right now..?<p>
GDorsey1:     Copper and oil are by far my favorites.<p>
GLSUTER:     Forest Oil Corp. (FOIL). Hold or sell??<p>
GDorsey1:     Forest Oil will also benefit in the coming paradigm, but the real fire will be in the drillers.<p>
BABY SOROS:     So PC manufacturers will get hurt, I agree, which companies will get hurt the most?<p>
GDorsey1:     Gateway and Dell are good shorts here.<p>
BABY SOROS:     Great, I'm short DELL. What is your reasoning- price wars upon us, lack of demand, why?<p>
GDorsey1:     Lack of demand. Japanese entering market, cutting into margins.<p>
BABY SOROS:     Man it's scary I have the same reasoning-- Greg you think shorting is the way, or puts for the average small investor?<p>
GDorsey1:     The problem with puts is time value erosion while you're waiting for the decline.<p>
BABY SOROS:     I agree Greg, but it's hard sometimes for average investor to find stock to short, so long-term puts only way.<p>
Mav1579:     I have 1500 shares of DEC, 2000 shares of T,  2000 KM,  1000 AOL, 2000 BS. What's your opinion?<p>
GDorsey1:     No offense to our gracious host, but I wouldn't touch AOL. T is a winner. DEC may be OK long term.<p>
Taccat2:     GREG  are you familiar with ASTEC?<p>
GDorsey1:     ASTEC Industries:  from a value point of view is very cheap, but be patient.<p>
Charchy:     Do you believe in buying H & R Block before tax season? I happen to be a C.P.A.<p>
GDorsey1:     No, earnings are already factored into share price. No seasonal play.<p>
AGrace7945:     Greg  your opinion on PD - Phelps Dodge - thanks.<p>
GDorsey1:     Phelps also looks good, a more conservative play than Asarco.<p>
Dan M999:     What do you think about TXN?<p>
GDorsey1:     I like TXN. Buy now.<p>
Mav1579:     What about XOMA?<p>
GDorsey1:     XOMA, I don't know why it's down so much. Not real thrilled with pattern for small biotech.<p>
MackMufi:     What about Bay Networks?<p>
GDorsey1:     Other networking companies offer better opportunities--Cisco for example.<p>
BABY SOROS:     Mack- I like BAY, if you care, they finally have strong management and good products.<p>
Gbullpin:     Sun Glass Hut International?<p>
GDorsey1:     It will be a long time before Sun Glass reaches old highs. Might be a short-term trade for a few points.<p>
Nogoth6430:     Greg, how about ADT?<p>
GDorsey1:     Crime's up. Gotta love it.<p>
Nogoth6430:     Any target on price on ADT?<p>
GDorsey1:     25 in the next six months.<p>
MackMurfi:     Will Republic Ind. hit 35 by Jan.?<p>
GDorsey1:     Republic could hit 35 by the new year.<p>
RKanterman:     Greg, do you think CAKE can finally get it together?<p>
GDorsey1:     CAKE is fairly valued after recent decline...hold.<p>
JPULTZ10:     What's your short term thoughts on GNTA and CLYS?
?
GDorsey1:     Genta, a bit small and way too speculative for my tastes.<p>
SBonner627:     What do you think of USBS?<p>
GDorsey1:     USBS looks interesting. It's a buy here.<p>
Gbullpin:     How about Adelphia?<p>
GDorsey1:     Is that cable TV?<p>
Gbullpin:     Yes, cable service, too.<p>
GDorsey1:     Balance sheet looks ugly. Years away from any sort of earnings. Avoid.<p>
HKirschenm:     Any opinion on High Plains (HIPC)?<p>
GDorsey1:     High Plains's undervaluation mystifies me.<p>
BILVOL:     How about Novellus?<p>
GDorsey1:     I like Novellus. Overseas sales should ensure strong earnings. Buy.<p>
Nogoth6430:     What is your out look on AAPL?<p>
GDorsey1:     Apple always shines a faint light of hope. Japanese buyout probable in next few years. Decent speculation.<p>
Dan M999:     Greg, what do you think about AMD?<p>
GDorsey1:     AMD is an also-ran. Buy Intel.<p>
AK716:     How about TRV?<p>
GDorsey1:     TRV not likely to set world aflame, but good company.<p>
JOKECAAM:     USAir announced today it was buying upwards of maybe 400 planes.  Is this a stock to buy? I've heard USAir may go to 28-30.  Now at 18-19.  What do you think?<p>
GDorsey1:     No faith in the carrier.<p>
WorthEdit1:     That's all the time we have. Thank you, Greg, for your insights, and thanks to all of you for joining us for this evening's "Conference Call."<p>
GDorsey1:     Good night and thanks for coming.<p>
WorthEdit1:     Greg, tell them how they can get your newsletter.<p>
GDorsey1:     Visit www.investars.com.<p>
WorthEdit1:     It's a great service--we at Worth OnLine subscribe! Once again, thank you, Greg for taking the time to be here tonight.<p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
