				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>10/02/96 -- Henry Weingarten, Astrologers Fund Inc., New York</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						On Wednesday, October 2, Henry Weingarten joined Worth OnLine for a live "Conference Call." Financial astrologer Weingarten uses interplanetary analysis to predict the market's twists and turns. Among his prophecies have been the Tokyo Market Crash, the day the DJIA broke 3000, the day gold broke 400, and the '89 mini-crash. Weingarten's Astrologers Fund Inc., New York, is introducing three funds next year--the Jupiter Fund (growth) and the Saturn Fund (value/income), and the Pluto Fund (hedge). He is also the author of "Investing by the Stars." Follows is a transcript of the evening's chat, edited for clarity. The opinions expressed are Henry Weingarten's, and do not reflect the views of Worth, Worth OnLine, or Capital Publishing. <p>
WorthEdit3 : Welcome to "Conference Call," Worth OnLine's live chat show series. Every week we give readers the opportunity to chat with the leaders in money and markets. Check our site (Keyword: Worth) for a calendar of upcoming events. Tonight, Henry Weingarten will discuss what's in the stars for the overall market, individual sectors, and specific stocks.<p>
WorthEdit1 : Okay, Henry, I'm going to start with a tough one. Some say this astrology thing is a ruse. What do you say to the non-believers?<p>
AFund      : Well I was an astrologer for 20 years BEFORE doing the markets. Wrote several books etc. on the subject. Also my forecasting record is outstanding as seen on our Web site -- articles and forum on AOL. So while obviously good for marketing, IT WORKS.<p>
Markets are determined by
1) fundamentals
2) technicals
3) market timing and psychology 
4) is CHARTED by astrology<p>
Probergum  : What are your feelings about the market after the election?<p>
AFund      : DOWN DOWN DOWN. That is for November. Of course we go up again with January-March, then down again.<p>
AFund      : I believe November a very down month for lots of reasons -- both astro and non-astro. Non- astro -- fed will raise November 13. Even if they don't -- market will be afraid until then. End of October, market afraid because of uncertainty of election. Also there are astro reasons November down. But we are know markets NEVER GO DOWN so WILL BE UP in January and February. Thereafter March on-- don't bet on it!!! We will be shorting more than currently!!!<p>
RWaldock   : Do you come to the same conclusions as Arch Crawford?<p>
AFund      : I don't know Arch's opinions all the time, but recently he wrote that we agreed THIS TIME. However Arch is more pessimistic about the world than I believe I am. I always feel like an optimist when I talk with Arch.<p>
WorthEdit1 : TSalem3368 asked : What's good play tomorrow?<p>
AFund      : Actually wasn't playing anything tomorrow -- we made a lot on a short on a company that all of us are familiar with -- won't mention names, but was 35 on Monday :) Currently need 30 :) Actually BEST PLAY: I would say to write November calls on OEX if that is your type of play. Also like silver (physical). Will think of some others shortly.<p>
RWaldock   : Are you bullish till November?<p>
AFund      : No, see October as trading month -- with downward basis -- that is to end 5959 (77 X 77) quite high -- most professionals scared sh**. Little good valuation. Maybe 6000 -- maybe 6100, but so what? Risk/reward terrible. I would say we will be lower end of month than now and we are Just looking for good shorts in general, except some special microcap plays.<p>
Serpay     : What's a Pisces to invest in these days<p>
AFund      : Pisces question too general Serpay.  Based on whole horoscope!!!!<p>
WorthEdit1 : How much does the INVESTOR's sign matter in this market?<p>
AFund      : Signs don't matter MUCH. Some people are VERY much like their signs -- I am a LEO for example, a textbook Leo. I like markets because I get to be right every day (almost :) In a moment will give you a perfect play for Leos but some people are not also moon, ascendant, and planets play a role. Much too general need time, place, and date of birth to see whole chart, then can judge. Some details in Investing by the Stars by Henry Weingarten. ALSO best astrological trade? Buy a Leo for what he/she is worth. Sell them for what they think they are worth!!! <p>
RWaldock   : Where do you see Nasdaq and Dow bottoming out next year and when?<p>
AFund      : Who said next year is a bottom, maybe 98. Seven years often down years but 8 not necessarily up. No recession for a long time. Too long a time most economists and I agree see one next year or two -- I emphasize two!!! Certainly we can go to 5000 EASILY and 1000 on Nasdaq. Remember with Jupiter, Uranus and Jupiter Neptune conjunction in 1997. This will be PEAK FOR MARKET then more realistic as time goes on. You think the markets always go up -- remember 1980's real estate always went up. Never lost in real estate until... Well, same with stock market. However...always good plays. If you bought real estate in 1987 may or may NOT be even without inflation. Will be same for markets -- in next two years!!!<p>
WorthEdit1 : How heavily do you weight astrology in your overall analysis of a stock?<p>
AFund      : I am primarily a financial astrologer. I do charts of incorporation and times of first listing, sometimes also CEO or key personnel. I also look at technicals and investing in trading mostly astrology and technicals in investing mostly fundamentals and astrology. That is my edge the market surprises!!!!<p>
Serpay     : Does the Sign of A CEO affect your decisions on stocks?<p>
AFund      : Signs-- no his whole horoscope, but only if identified with company or a start up. Many times CEO is creamed and stock goes up right? Other times, golden parachute and stock tanks. If identified like Lee Iacocca with Chrysler etc., then yes.<p>
SISU SUE   : What microcaps look good to you?<p>
AFund      : We are looking at a number of junior gold and anyone who has ever visited my site knows I love IHI -- my favorite stock pick, the next Microsoft. Also the baby AQX.A just 25 undervalued more 150%. But check out keyword: astrologers fund for a number of picks. But if just one  V.IHI or IHITF. 1-800-838-8090. Check it out.<p>
AWENCH3373 : Should my astrological chart be in sync with a company I want to invest in?<p>
AFund      : A Wench- depends. If you are running the company, yes. If you are a major shareholder, yes! If you want to buy at a good time, yes. But in general no, however if you ever sell a stock that goes up right afterwards or vice versa your horoscope's NOT in sync. For long term holdings and major holdings, yes. Wear a portfolio like clothing -- you should be comfortable with it. Besides, an awful lot of work to chart for some companies we look at the buyers' horoscopes!!! When buying a small cap company, look at your chart. If it goes well you will probably do well. <p>
WorthEdit1 : Can you give us your international outlook?<p>
AFund      : Yes! love Japan for 1997. Called the top and bottoms in those markets in my book. For example, yen UNDERVALUED. So Japan #1 for 1997. Mid-1998-1999  I like Italy -- lire undervalued now. And I like Canada -- 1997 again. And Australian/New Zealand real estate in the next few years, due to Asian money pouring in.<p>
BeyReg     : I am an astrologer, but I do not practice financial astrology -- any hints??<p>
AFund      : 1) read my book Investing by the Stars
2) go to conferences November 1/2  in NYC and May 16-18 NYC
3) read other books
4) get books with horoscopes of DJIA and S&P 500 and take one or two examples and try to predict. When successful, another one or two. When successful, put up REAL MONEY!!!! TEST, most ideas don't work. Will be posting interesting study in Britain in markets which had several failures of popular theories, not mine!!!!<p>
Antonia123 : Gold...time to buy or sell? What do the stars say?<p>
AFund      : Gold I LOVE gold  -- ONLY GOLD IS AS GOOD AS GOLD. Wait till after November games are over XAU 173+ that's more than 50% in 8 months, especially after January. Silver even better. Of course until November watch out for Rubin/IMF Games we do have inflation. Anyone eaten recently? Bought gas etc.? Only computers down :) <p>
Joshi1111:  Any stocks under $10? <p>
AFund      : Josh under $10 -- why not IHI only 1.75?<p>
MF Value   : AFund... XAU at 173... I doubt it. Especially not by the end of the year.<p>
AFund      : MF value- I called both days gold took out 400 and top day at under 420. I called last two moves on XAU could be wrong. But wait until May -- if so, then tell me I'm wrong. Okay to doubt but that is good sign no one wants gold, very small market cap under coke size. So little goes very, very long way. Also don't forget Yeltsin, China, Middle East, US dollar... we will see!!!<p>
MF Value   : Well... I've bought puts twice in 4 months when it hits 130+. Haven't suffered yet. Actually covered the other day at 115.<p>
AFund      : Hey two ways to make money, MF, up or down? Traders do it both ways.<p>
Joshi1111  : Why do you pick IHI, and its expected price?<p>
AFund      : IHI is the next Microsoft -- International Hi-Tech Industries. This is a revolutionary process totally different. <p>
Joshi1111  : Do you have a toll-free number? <p>
AFund      : I do not -- have forum on AOL keyword: astrologers fund or Web site www.afund.com. Anyways, there is an IHI posting there which tells my views, why I think it's going to $10, then $30, then $100!! Read it there! Or call company for details and check it out yourself.<p>
SLSheehan  : How has lunar eclipse in Taurus affected the market?<p>
AFund      : Well, Taurus is the sign of NYSE. <p>
JodyWilli  : Do you think the eclipse will trigger a downturn?<p>
AFund      : But has to be same degree area -- which eclipse triggers volatility in markets? Often today a 100 point play in a day or two. Also triggers UP moves. Depends on planets involved or between eclipses.<p>
JodyWilli  : With Saturn moving onto the US 5th house cusp, what do you think this will mean?<p>
AFund      : Jody don't use houses so can't answer that question -- use angles only. <p>
BeyReg     : I have Taurus in my 12th - good for investing? <p>
AFund      : Taurus on 12th same thing not my style of astrology-see Study of Astrology, for example.<p>
WorthEdit3 : KaiPorter asked: do you avoid investing on certain points in the cycle that involve emotionalism such as Pisces.<p>
AFund      : Depends on whether you believe in market timing, also depends on which investments. I do market timing and global stock selection. There, I believe I can time market reasonably well. But also as a trader we go both ways. I would certainly be leery of putting NEW money in now. There are also tax issues in selling. Last week, we close-wrote calls on LU, a few weeks earlier on SL I agree cash is fine from these points. Garzarelli a little too early, but advice VERY very sound.<p>
Rplusd     : Hi everyone. Can the astrologer tell me what will  happen to mortgage rates in December?<p>
AFund      : In general we see rates going up through midyear -- then stabilizing and down as we enter into a recession. So the earlier the better to lock in rates. Also real estate will outperform stock market next year. Hard assets better than physical assets in 1997-98 in our opinion.<p>
WorthEdit1 : TestyDi asks about the outlook for oil and energy stocks. <p>
AFund      : Testy: oil okay till January but near end of this cycle -- we are cashing out and hedging oil positions a bit early.<p>
TEBOMAN    : Southern California real estate may never come back<p>
AFund      : TEB speaking of Real estate in general also pockets that are different same with stocks, but in general REITS giving 6-7%. Good investment today, such as SSS<p>
JodyWilli  : Do you think the govt. will be printing out more money next year? Have you looked at AT&T?<p>
AFund      : Jody- Government always prints money. Do follow ATTp -- would buy at 40. Sold at above 55. Lucent sold at 45. Would buy 30-35. T will do okay, not great. Same with MCD next year.<p>
JodyWilli  : I mean because of not being able to pay our loans?<p>
AFund      : Jody- as to loan of US dollar is peaking and in trouble. Haven't done astrological work yet. I do this December 7 each year in my annual report.<p>
JodyWilli  : Thank you - I felt that too and needed validation.<p>
AFund      : BUT little upward move and some bond trouble in the not distant future.<p>
MF Value   : AFund... do you think you actually call the markets better than those fancy Wise men on Wall Street...?<p>
AFund      : As we both know 79-81% of people underperform indexes. The astrologers are in the 19-21%.<p>
MF Value   : The stars tell you what companies and industries are going to do well...?<p>
JodyWilli  : MF Value - check out latest survey of advisors on Wall Street -- all consistently wrong! <p>
AFund      : Only problem is playing against chickens and monkeys, not dartboard of other money managers!<p>
MF Value   : You can make calls on the 11 stocks that make up the XAU by the stars...?<p>
AFund      : MF just the stars tell me what companies and industries as do my other fundamentals and technical resources. I track the XAU index by the birth of the index; don't play individual ones -- this is co-checked with silver and gold horoscopes.<p>
RWaldock   : peak?<p>
AFund      : Don't play the in same way as NYSE, but expect it early next year at least the technology sector with Jupiter/Uranus in February. Excessive valuations will retreat<p>
MIB42      : Do you have an investment fund letter?<p>
AFund      : I do not do an investment newsletter. I am a money manager. We have forums on AOL keyword: astrologers fund or www.afund.com. Also have a mailing list you can E-mail, it is free. We have hedge funds and some public SEC-approved funds to be released next year. Currently manage money for high net worth individuals.<p>
SLSheehan  : AFund--How about Iomega (IOMG), makers of Zip and Jaz? <p>
AFund      : IOMG will be in trouble. We called the top to the day at 55. Looking for shorts in the 27-30 range -- watch out IOMG. Remember they have strong competition next year. If in, I would advise getting out at 25-30 if you are that lucky again. IOMG is in trouble NOW!!!!! Look at our May 23 report to the day we sent out to thousand at 55. Probably one or two more times, then covered and then reshort etc.<p>
Joshi1111  : Penny stocks???????? 1-3 months<p>
AFund      : Joshi penny stocks some up some down. Depends on the PROMOTER!!!! AS MUCH AS HOROSCOPE!!!!! Anyway, those games over NEXT year.<p>
RWaldock   : If market is bad in 1997, will your funds sell short?<p>
AFund      : Of course we will sell short. Of course we buy special situations. But more shorting next year, first write calls then short then buy puts depends on how close to the number of down times<p>
JodyWilli  : IOMG's chart looked bad around the 18th of this month -- did you look around that date?<p>
AFund      : Playing at moment technically -- more than astrologically sometimes you don't need astrology to make money, although astrology ALWAYS helps.<p>
PVinny     : Anyone have some light to shed on HWP - I am long 2000 shares and its seems it time to sell.<p>
AFund      : HWP: a little past time, but you have good profit. We were in for almost two years, less up room now, lots of Japanese competition coming so cover soon.<p>
RWaldock   : When will you have prospectuses available and where?<p>
AFund      : RW E-mail me, can't offer yet.<p>
JodyWilli  : AFund - save time, what stocks do you like for this month?<p>
AFund      : Jody this is mostly time for trading -- not investing. Buy in late November/early December for one last big blow out. But why buy here -- where is value- not Planet Hollywood :) This is trading month with downwards basis. November down down down for new people. Our aids play in ENZ about 19- at 22+ we stop loss.<p>
RWaldock   : What are your annual returns? Range?<p>
AFund      : RW depends on clients. We have some with large gains and others more conservative, individualized by client portfolio.<p>
Tryme18182 : What does astrology say of this month?<p>
AFund      : Good question. Eventually a few winners but next two years (fundamentally) ALL ARE IN TROUBLE. Will lose money, so avoid!!!!!!! Or buy only on traditional value (not here). However in 1998 forward YES BUY BUY BUY. But not now -- will lose money, not make it .Too much competition needs to go dead first.<p>
JBelang    : What about Intel?<p>
AFund      : Intel good company obviously, but that is a sector we are looking to short. Microsoft as close to 150 as we can get, IBM at 135 as close as we get. INTL not yet, but after Jupiter/Uranus and with Japanese who knows? These are momentum plays and some fundamental. I am a cosmic VALUE player. Where is value? Show me? I see little!<p>
RWaldock   : What main factor will start the 1997 decline?<p>
AFund      : Good question: stopped making that guess a long time ago. More important to know WHEN than why. I can think of lots of reasons. But will be a triple whammy to get these crazy people out of the market. My guesses are: less than 10 billion market inflow, two lots of call buying, and then a trigger -- war, assignation, bond default, etc. which will get the blame. An inflation number of Reality for example would do it. <p>
SLSheehan  : AFund -- You say it's more important to know when than why, you said, so WHEN do stocks plunge?<p>
AFund      : They do in a series. Remember, everyone knows stocks only go up and every dip is a buying opportunity. So a phased down move 1: November, move 2: March, move 3: read my December report! <p>
Joshi1111  : Any other stocks under $10?<p>
AFund      : Joshi write me- CCRI will go about another 35% in the next two months. E-mail me and will figure out a few.<p>
CrookManor : What do you see as the stable stocks of the future, aka Wal-mart of the present?<p>
AFund      : Crook VERY good Q: make a shopping list of good quality stocks, then make a wish list of price and wait!!!!! You may not get all but you will get some. Lots of GOOD COMPANIES OUT THERE, but very very few good prices of stock. So choose your list and when they are dumped in next year's vicious rotation cycle, buy buy buy. Remember even if market up -- they will rotate them viciously this year.<p>
CHOP180    : Any opinions on CAI Wireless Systems  CAWS?<p>
AFund      : NO don't track CAI.<p>
JTaylor815 : What do you think of Wind River?<p>
AFund      : Same -- don't track<p>
CrookManor : Do you recommend buying from these recent hot IPO's??<p>
AFund      : IPO's unless in early are good short candidates!!!! If you get in right time -- before than you make like LU at 27 otherwise more tricky but most lose about 6 months -- no astrology here -- so chart them.<p>
Please check out my Web site, forum on AOL, read my book and E-mail me if you have more questions.<p>
WorthEdit1 : Alright, I think Henry's typing fingers are about to fall off. Thanks, Henry, for the lively chat!<p>
AFund      : Now I leave you all with my question!!! CAN YOU AFFORD NOT TO HAVE A FINANCIAL ASTROLOGER IN YOUR FUTURE?<p>
WorthEdit3 : That Concludes this edition of "Conference Call," Worth OnLine's live weekly chat series. The Worth staff extends its appreciation to Henry Weingarten for being our guest this evening.<p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
