		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>04/16/96 -- Jim Jubak, Author of "The Worth Guide to Electronic Investing"</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						On Tuesday, April 16, Worth's senior financial editor, Jim Jubak, joined Worth OnLine for a live chat show. During the hour and fifteen minute chat, Jubak answered readers' questions about the stock market, investing, and the outlook for interest rates. <p>
WorthJubak : 
Hi, this is Jim Jubak. I've just signed on as WorthJubak. We're open for business.<p>
WorthEdit1 : 
Jim Jubak, Worth's senior financial editor is with us live. Jim, I would like to welcome you to tonight's chat.<p>
WorthJubak : 
Sure enough. So what did you think of the rally today. Really better for Nasdaq than the Dow.<p>
JSHDFR     : 
How much did it go up? I missed the closing figures.<p>
WorthJubak : 
Hello, JSHDFR. The Dow was up about 25, Nasdaq about 14 to a new high.<p>
WorthEdit1 : 
In the May cover story, "Can This Market Be Trusted," you say that the strength of the current market is based on the expectations and behavior of investors. How so?<p>
DewDood    : 
Please comment on Cirrus Logic, PepsiCo, T. Rowe Price, Schwab stocks.....Jim, are you here to talk about stocks?<p>
WorthJubak : 
Well, DewDood, I'm glad to tell you what I know about stocks, but I won't give buys or sells.<p>
DewDood    : 
Jim, what can you tell me about PepsiCo?<p>
WorthJubak : 
DewDood, to bounce back to Pepsi, it seems they've got some problems competing overseas with Coke.<p>
DewDood    : 
Do you think that Coke's reliance on overseas income will be detrimental with the increasing strength of the dollar?<p>
PURITRON   : 
What's with the telephone stocks?<p>
WorthJubak : 
Puritron, I think the days when one thing was "with" all telephones are over.<p>
PURITRON   : 
What is your opinion of WordCom?<p>
WorthJubak : 
Puritron, never heard of it, what does it do?<p>
PURITRON   : 
It's the fourth largest telephone company.<p>
Kaypatel   : 
Jim, what do you think about Diamond Multimedia?<p>
WorthJubak : 
Kaypatel, I don't follow the company in depth. I know people who like it, others think it's pricey.<p>
Realdonna  : 
Read the article about the bubble theory...does the theory make a case for contrarianism??<p>
WorthJubak : 
Realdonna, only in a very specific way. You certainly can't "fight the tape" in this market.<p>
Realdonna  : 
Define your "specific way."<p>
WorthJubak : 
Realdonna, To be a contrarian you might have to invest in something other than stocks, real estate.<p>
Realdonna  : 
OK...so for us who are hooked on the idea of equities for "wealth", what do we do to protect?<p>
WorthJubak : 
Realdonna, in what time frame?<p>
Realdonna  : 
Always a tough decision...think long term...but cannot avoid worrying about short!!<p>
WorthJubak : 
Realdonna: Okay, but what's long term to you? <p>
Realdonna  : 
Some money is in for 10 years or more...but some will be needed in 2-5. <p>
DewDood    : 
Jim, what do you know about Cirrus Logic?????<p>
FEJersey   : 
JIM, WHAT IS YOUR OPINION ABOUT HOLDING MICRON TECH STOCKS?<p>
WorthJubak : 
FEJersey, I believe Michael Murphy on Micron. He thinks they're a commodity chipmaker. Not good.<p>
Kaypatel   : 
Jim, what do you think about S3? Both of my stocks Diamond Multimedia and S3 are hit very badly. Should I hold or sell?<p>
WorthEdit1 : 
Kaypatel--Jim says he will answer questions about stocks he knows, but will not do buys or sells.<p>
Jshively12 : 
Jim,  any thoughts about Merisel (Computer Reseller)?<p>
Buzzard580 : 
What role does foreign money have in the current "bubble?"<p>
ENavori    : 
Hello Jim, your recent article in Worth was very informative. How about Reits?<p>
WorthJubak : 
ENavori, REITs tend to be interest rate sensitive. I'd look for one without big exposure to offices.<p>
Buzzard580 : 
Will the bubble burst after the election?<p>
WorthJubak : 
Depends on how much of this bubble is related to capital gains tax cut hopes.<p>
Buzzard580 : 
What about Greenspan just protecting his job?<p>
WorthJubak : 
I'm not a big Greenspan fan. I think the Fed's been lucky that Japan tanked.<p>
Buzzard580 : 
But isn't it Japan's money that's keeping interest rates down?<p>
WorthJubak : 
Exactly, so Greenspan's been running a tight money policy at the Fed except for foreign $.<p>
Buzzard580 : 
But if Japan tanked, then where was the lost wealth?<p>
WorthJubak : 
Much of the lost wealth is still on bank balance sheets in Japan for a write-off.<p>
TuckerDg   : 
Jim, Any thoughts on merchant banking funds? Can they beat the market over 5 years? <p>
HPG1       : 
What do you think about Dow Dividend Strategy & "Select 10"?<p>
DewDood    : 
Jim, what are your thoughts on interest rates in the next 12 months?<p>
WorthJubak : 
DewDood, I think rates will probably come down a bit over the next quarter but then head back up.<p>
ENavori    : 
Jim, do you favor any sector of stocks -like oil exploration or refining?<p>
DewDood    : 
Jim, is the economy really picking up?<p>
HomerC226  : 
How do you know when the right time to invest is?<p>
RuthsBill  : 
