Is there a publication called "Who's Who on Wall Street"?<p>
POOTERPUTT : 
But is inflation going to be the real fuel for gold? Or will a political upheaval be it?<p>
Buzzard580 : 
Clinton is a loser.<p>
DryClean10 : 
Dole will take it home.<p>
POOTERPUTT : 
Dole?  How about Perot?<p>
BeachBoyX8 : 
Forget politics please !!!!<p>
POOTERPUTT : 
Sorry Beach, we had to bring it up because it effects the market.<p>
Buzzard580 : 
And there are many theories related to who's the next prez.<p>
BeachBoyX8 : 
Besides Worth, which financial magazines or journals do you read?<p>
WorthJubak : 
BeachBoy I read Barrons, CA. Tech Stock Letter. Thanks a lot every body for dropping by.  Good night.<p>
WorthEdit1 : 
Thanks you Jim for this lively chat.<p>
JSHFDR  :
Thanks, Jim.<p>
PStan9530  : 
Thanks.<p>
WorthEdit1 : 
And thank you everyone for your great questions.<p>
POOTERPUTT : 
Thanks Jim.<p>
MHS85      : 
Since we all pay homage to the DOW, and IBM's such a big part of it, which way IBM?<p>
POOTERPUTT : 
North on IBM<p>
MHS85      : 
How far north?<p>
POOTERPUTT : 
155-175 over a 2-3 year holding period.<p>
MHS85      : 
Then the DOW does reach 6000!<p>
Buzzard580 : 
Thanks Jim<p>
WorthEdit1 : 
A transcript of this event will be posted in the TODAY window on our opening screen.<p>
BeachBoyX8 : 
Alright- good night !!! <p>
DryClean10 : 
Night Jim<p>
WorthEdit1 : 
You can get a schedule of our online events by subscribing to our FREE weekly E-mail newsletter. It is called "A Week's Worth." It also has a schedule of our daily features and stories you won't find anywhere on the site. Read Jim's latest story for Worth, "Can This Market Be Trusted," online right now. You'll find it in the TODAY window. Also look for his predictions about a market bubble on Friday--"How To Beat a Bubble."<p>
POOTERPUTT : 
See how the theory works.  It's like magic. Ha, Ha.<p>
MHS85      : 
And the good thing about your Bubble article is you have at least a 50-50 chance of being right.<p>
WorthEdit1 : 
MHS85--right! Worth and Worth OnLine's editors would like to hear from you. You can post your questions and comments on our message boards. We check them regularly. Also E-mail questions to our Editor, John Koten. He writes a weekly column that appears on Wednesdays. You can post questions for him on "The Editor's Files" message board.<p>
POOTERPUTT : 
MHS85- gotta go.  Talk to you later<p>
MHS85      : 
Good night.<p>
WorthEdit1 : 
Thank you all for coming. Great questions. Good chat. We plan to host online chats weekly. I am working on lining up some important guests.
					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
