<p>Message Posted by <p><a href="mailto:HTrinidad@vax2.rainis.net">H. Trinidad</a> on February 08, 1997 at 16:07:45:<p>
Are there any stock <br>market anomalies <br>besides Value Line <br>and the Dow 5 and <br>10 theories?  <p>Also, I'd like your <br>thoughts on James <br>O'Shaughnessy's <br>Book "What Works <br>On Wall Street" <br>According to <br>O'Shaughnessy, the <br>best portfolio of all <br>is his united <br>portfolio in which <br>he screens for <br>stocks with a Price <br>to Sales Ratio of <br>less than 1.5 and <br>then buys the top <br>50 stocks with the <br>best 1 year price <br>appreciation. <br>Therefore, he is <br>mixing value(PSR) <br>and growth <br>(relative strength) <br>which produces <br>double digit returns <br>that beat the <br>market with a <br>standard deviation <br>just a tad higher <br>than the market.  <br>
<br>
<p><hr width=75%>
<center>[ <a href="http://www.worth.com/forums/talktoworth/lynch/worthboard.html">Return to the Front of this Board</a> ]</center>
