Are there any stock <br>market anomalies <br>besides Value Line <br>and the Dow 5 and <br>10 theories?  <p>Also, I'd like your <br>thoughts on James <br>O'Shaughnessy's <br>Book "What Works <br>On Wall Street" <br>According to <br>O'Shaughnessy, the <br>best portfolio of all <br>is his united <br>portfolio in which <br>he screens for <br>stocks with a Price <br>to Sales Ratio of less <br>than 1.5 and then <br>buys the top 50 <br>stocks with the best <br>1 year price <br>appreciation. <br>Therefore, he is <br>mixing value(PSR) <br>and growth (relative <br>strength) which <br>produces double <br>digit returns that <br>beat the market with <br>a standard deviation <br>just a tad higher <br>than the market.  <br>
