    <title>Demographics</title>
  </head>
  <body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000">
<table cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5 width=550>
<tr>
	<td width=390>
 <a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6001.html?worth+PCFN18.gif+Message%20Boards>
<img src="/ads/PCFN18.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>

	</td>
	<td width=150 valign=top> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width=390 valign=top>
<center>
<p>
<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b><p>
<pre>
</pre>
</center>
<blockquote>
    <center>
      <h1>Demographics</h1>
    </center>
<hr width=75%>
<center>[ <a href="http://www.worth.com/forums/talktoworth/lynch/worthboard.html">Return to the Front of this Board</a> ]</center>
<p>Message Posted by <p><a href="mailto:Remarkl@msn.com">Lawrence Kramer</a> on January 29, 1997 at 13:18:30:<p>
Do you agree that much of the current run-up in the averages is the result of baby-boomers saving for retirement, i.e., essentially a matter of the demand for stocks outstripping the supply, with the resulting run-up then fueling the demand even further?<p>If so, do you think that the current high real long-term U.S. interest rates are in part a result of "distorted" asset allocations by U.S. savers who are chasing the high returns of the stock market.  (The strength of the dollar suggests that the rest of the world thinks our bonds are a bargain.) <p>If so, when will this worm turn, and how violent will the correction be?  I foresee the day when the boomers realize that they do not have enough time to recoup the losses implicit in a correction and all run for bonds at once, creating in the process the very bear they are fleeing.  And I foresee it before the day they start liquidating their holdings to support them in their old age, i.e., sooner, rather than later. <p>What do you think?
<br>
<p><hr width=75%>
<center>[ <a href="http://www.worth.com/forums/talktoworth/lynch/worthboard.html">Return to the Front of this Board</a> ]</center>
</blockquote>
</td><td width=150 valign=top>
<center><img src="/imgs/messageyellow.gif"></center>	</td>
	</tr>
<tr><td width=390><center>
