In one of your articles you referred to <br>JNJ as the best growth stock of all <br>time. That comment stuck with me, and I <br>am the proud owner of 200 shares (it <br>just split). I have done real well and <br>consider it a real "base" for my <br>portfolio. Do you still think it will <br>continue to be a dynamic growth stock in <br>the next ten years??<br> I have missed not seeing your articles <br>for the last couple of months.<p>Thanks,<br>Jack
